===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''[[vis]]'', screw, winding stairs, from Old French[[Category:Old French derivations]] <!--[[w:Old French|Old French]][[Category:Old French derivations]]--> ''vis'', ''viz'', from {{L.}} ''[[vitis]]'', vine; probably akin to English[[Category:English derivations]] '''[[withy]]'''.

===Noun===
'''vise''' (''plural'' '''vises''')

====Alternative spellings====
*'''vice''' (''Commonwealth English'')

#(''US'') An [[instrument]] consisting of two [[jaw]]s, closing by a screw, [[lever]], [[cam]], or the like, for holding work, as in filing.

